A contusion, also known as a bruise, is a region of injured tissue usually with purple discoloration.
Gêng-hoeh, mā ē-sái kóng o͘-chheⁿ, sī tio̍h-siong ê cho͘-chit chhut-hiān o͘-o͘ chheⁿ-chheⁿ ê hoa-pan.
A decoration and a distraction for bored patients.
Chng-sek-phín, mā ē-sái gô͘-lo̍k kám-kak bô-liâu ê hoān-chiá
A decoration, other objects can be placed on top.
Chng-sek-phín, pa̍t-ê bu̍t-phín ē-sái khǹg tī bīn-téng.
A fistula is an abnormal anatomical connection between two hollow spaces.
Tī-lāu sī tī kái-phò-ha̍k siōng nn̄g-ê khang bô chèng-siông ê liâm chòe-hóe.
A hospital with General Surgery, Internal Medicine and Orthopaedy departments, 96 x 96
Chi̍t-ê ū It-poaⁿ Gōa-kho, Lāi-kho kah Chéng-hêng gōa-kho ê pēⁿ-īⁿ, 96 x 96
A peptic ulcer is an open lesion in the lining of the stomach, duodenum or esophagus.
Siau-hòa-sèng-ùi-iông sī chi̍t-chióng tī ūi, cha̍p-jī-chí-tn̂g a̍h-sī chia̍h-tō lāi-bīn ê khai-hòng-sèng pīⁿ-piàn.
A peptic ulcer is an open lesion in the lining of the stomach, duodenum or esophagus. It is most commonly caused by the bacterium h. pylori or prolonged, excessive use of NSAIDs

Siau-hòa-sèng-ùi-iông sī chi̍t-chióng tī ūi, cha̍p-jī-chí-tn̂g a̍h-sī chia̍h-tō lāi-bīn ê khai-hòng-sèng pīⁿ-piàn. It-poaⁿ lâi-kóng kám-jiám sè-khún h. pylori a̍h-sī iōng siuⁿ-chē NSAID ē tì-sú chit-khoán pēⁿ.
A ruptured appendix can be fatal and thus appendicitis is one of the most common reasons for abdominal surgery.
Piak-phòa ê thâng-iūⁿ-sûi hoān-sè ē tì-miā, só͘-í Thâng-iūⁿ-sûi-iām sī chi̍t-hāng khui pak-tó͘ to siōng chia̍p-khòaⁿ ê lí-iû.
Chi̍t-ê ū kip-chín ê sè pēⁿ-īⁿ, 64 x 64
A small hospital with General Surgery department, 64 x 64
Chi̍t-ê ū It-poaⁿ gōa-kho ê sè pēⁿ-īⁿ, 64 x 64
A small hospital with Orthopaedy department, 64 x 64
Chi̍t-ê ū Chéng-hêng gōa-kho ê sè pēⁿ-īⁿ, 64 x 64

Acute renal failure refers to an abrupt loss of kidney function, effectively seizing the ability to filter the blood and produce urine. The causes can be many, but are usually due to extensive tissue damage or decreased kidney blood flow.

Kip-sèng io-chí sit-pāi sī kóng pō͘-pîn sit-khì io-chí ê ki-lêng, tiō sī lū hoeh chè-chō jiō ê châi-tiāu bô-khì ah. Che ū chiok chē ê goan-in, m̄-koh it-poaⁿ sī siuⁿ-chē ê cho͘-chit tio̍h-siong a̍h-sī lâi kàu io-chí ê hoeh-liû kiám-chió.
Amoebiasis is caused by Entamoeba histolytica, the infection spreads through water or food contaminated by feces.
Amoeba sèng chhiah-lī sī Entaoeba histolytica tì-sú ê, chit-chióng kám-jiám ē ùi hō͘ sái u-jiám ê chúi a̍h-sī chia̍h-mi̍h thoân-khui.
Anemia is defined as a reduced ability of the blood to carry oxygen.
Huih-hu ê tēng-gī sī huih-e̍k chhia sng-sò͘ ê lêng-le̍k kiám-chió.
Anemia is defined as a reduced ability of the blood to carry oxygen. This can be caused by a decrease in red blood cells or hemoglobin. Iron-deficiency anemia is the most common form of anemia.

Huih-hu ê tēng-gī sī huih-e̍k chhia sng-sò͘ ê lêng-le̍k kiám-chió. Che khó-lêng sī chhiah-hiuh-kiû a̍h-sī huih-sek-sò͘. kiám-chió khí-tì ê. Thih-chit khiàm-khoeh huih-hu sī siōng chia̍p-khòaⁿ ê huih-hu.

Anthrax is serious infection caused by the bacterium Bacillus anthracis. It is spread through the bacteria's spores. Contact is made typically by inhaling or eating the spores or through skin lesions.

Thòaⁿ-chhi chi̍t-chióng chin-hāi ê thoân-jiám pēⁿ, i goân-chū he kiò-chò Bacillus anthracis ê sè-khún. I sī ùi hit-ê sè-khún ê gê-pau thoân-khui. It-poaⁿ ê in-ūi khip-khì a̍h-sī chia̍h-tio̍h gê-pau a̍h-sī ùi phôe-hu pēⁿ-piàn ê só͘-chai chiap-chhiok tio̍h.
Appendicitis refers to infection in the appendix, which becomes obstructed and swollen.
Thâng-iūⁿ-sûi-iām sī kóng thâng-iūⁿ-sûi hoat-iām, hit-pêng ê piàn-chò pì-that koh chéng-tiùⁿ.
Appendicitis refers to infection in the appendix, which becomes obstructed and swollen. A ruptured appendix can be fatal and thus appendicitis is one of the most common reasons for abdominal surgery.

Thâng-iūⁿ-sûi-iām sī kóng thâng-iūⁿ-sûi hoat-iām, hit-pêng ê piàn-chò pì-that koh chéng-tiùⁿ. Piak-phòa ê thâng-iūⁿ-sûi hoān-sè ē tì-miā, só͘-í Thâng-iūⁿ-sûi-iām sī chi̍t-hāng khui pak-tó͘ to siōng chia̍p-khòaⁿ ê lí-iû.
Athlete’s foot, also called Tinea pedis, is a highly contagious skin infection of the feet caused by fungi.
Ūn-tōng-oân kha mā ē-sái kiò-chò Chiok-sián, sī chi̍t-chióng thoân-jiám-sèng chin kiông ê kha ê chin-khún phôe-hu kám-jiám.
Bacterial gastroenteritis is common gastrointestinal disease, in most cases lasting a few days.
Sè-khún-sèng ūi-tn̂g-iām sī chi̍t-chióng chiok chia̍p-khòaⁿ ê ūi-tn̂g-pēⁿ, tōa-pō͘-hūn ê lâng ē liân-sòa kúi-kang.
Bacterial tonsillitis is an infection of the tonsils.
Sè-khún-sèng píⁿ-thô-chôaⁿ-iām sī píⁿ-thô-chôaⁿ hō͘ kám-jiám.
Bacterial tonsillitis is an infection of the tonsils. The most common bacterial tonsillitis is caused by Streptococcus pyogenes, and is known as 'strep throat'.

Sè-khún-sèng píⁿ-thô-chôaⁿ-iām sī píⁿ-thô-chôaⁿ òe-tio̍h sè-khún. Siōng chia̍p-khòaⁿ ê sè-khún-sèng píⁿ-thô-chôaⁿ sī goân-chū chi̍t-chióng liân-só-chiōng kiû-khún (Streptococcus pyogenes), chit-ê pēⁿ mā hō͘ lâng kiò-chò "liân-só âu".
Basic clinical office for simple examinations and treatments.
Ki-pún ê mn̂g-chín pâng-keng hō͘ i-seng chò kán-tan ê kiám-cha kah tī-liâu.

Beef tapeworms (T. saginata) are parasitic flatworms living in the digestive system of humans. Cattle act as intermediate hosts when they consume fodder or water contaminated with human feces. Eating undercooked beef can cause infection.

Gû-bah tòa-thâng (T. saginata) sī chi̍t-chióng tòa tī lâng ê siau-hòa hē-thóng lāi ê kià-seng-sèng píⁿ-pîⁿ-thâng. Gû nā-sī chia̍h-tio̍h ū lâng sài ê chhī-liāu a̍h-sī chúi tiō ē piàn-chó i ê tiong-kan siok-chú. Chia̍h bô-se̍k ê gû-bah ū khó-lêng thoân-jiám.
Bladder stones can be formed in the bladder due to a mineralization of concentrated urine. There will only be symptoms if the flow of urine is compromised.
Phōng-kong kiat-chio̍h ē-sái tī phōng-kong lāi chek-chū ê jiō khòng-hoa āu hêng-sêng. Nā-sī jiō liông kiám-chió che kan-nā ē hông tòng-chò sī chèng-thâu niă.
Bronchitis is an inflammation of the lower airways called bronchi and is usually caused by virus.
Khì-kńg-chi-iām sī ē-bīn ê khì-kńg, tio̍h-sī khì-kńg-chi, hoat-iām. It-poaⁿ chit-ê pēⁿ sī pēⁿ-to̍k tì-sú ê.
Khí chi̍t-ê ū kong-lêng ê sè pēⁿ-īⁿ

Cat-scratch disease is a common infectious disease caused by Bartonella henselae. It is transmitted by cats, through the cat's scratch or bite. Presence of the bacteria in humans is hard to detect by traditional bacterial cultivation because growth takes up to 6 weeks.

Niau-jiàu-jia̍t sī chi̍t-chióng sè-khún Bartonella henselae tì-sú ê sò͘-siông thoân-jiám pēⁿ. I ē ùi niau jiàu-phòa a̍h-sī kā-phòa ê khang-chhùi li̍p--lâi. It-poaⁿ ê sè-khún pôe-ióng chiok pháiⁿ lia̍h-tio̍h chi̍t-chióng sè-khún, in-ūi i ài 6 lé-pài chiah ē seng-tióng.
Cattle act as intermediate hosts when they consume fodder or water contaminated with human feces.
Gû nā-sī chia̍h-tio̍h ū lâng sài ê chhī-liāu a̍h-sī chúi tiō ē piàn-chó i ê tiong-kan siok-chú.
Chickenpox, also known as varicella, is a highly contagious disease caused by the initial infection with Varicella zoster virus.
Chúi-chu mā hō͘ lâng kiò-chò varicella, sī chi̍t-chióng thoân-jiám-sèng chin kiông ê chi̍t-pēⁿ. Chit-ê pēⁿ goân-chū thâu-pái kám-jiám Varicella zoster pēⁿ-to̍k.

Chickenpox, also known as varicella, is a highly contagious disease caused by the initial infection with Varicella zoster virus. The disease results in a characteristic skin rash that forms small, itchy blisters, which eventually scab over.

Chúi-chu mā hō͘ lâng kiò-chò varicella, sī chi̍t-chióng thoân-jiám-sèng chin kiông ê chi̍t-pēⁿ. Chit-ê pēⁿ goân-chū thâu-pái kám-jiám Varicella zoster pēⁿ-to̍k. Chit-ê pēⁿ ē tì-sú lâng kui-seng-khu chhut phôe-chín, hêng-sêng sè-sè chhiah-ia̍h ê phā, siōng-bóe kian-phí.
Cholangitis is an infection of the bile duct usually caused by bacteria ascending from the duodenum. It occurs usually when the bile duct is already partially blocked by gallstones.
Táⁿ-kńg-iām it-poaⁿ sī táⁿ-kńg òe-tio̍h ùi cha̍p-jī-chí-tn̂g khí-khì ê sè-khún. It-poaⁿ lâi kóng che sī in-ūi táⁿ-kńg chá-tio̍h hō͘ táⁿ-chio̍h pō͘-hūn chó͘-tòng khì ah.
Cholecystitis is inflammation and infection of the gallbladder, usually due to blockage of the cystic duct by a gallstone.
Táⁿ-lông-iām sī táⁿ-lông hoat-iām kah táⁿ-lông òe-tio̍h. Che it-poaⁿ sī táⁿ-lông-kńg hō͘ táⁿ-chio̍h chó͘-tòng tio̍h.
Cholera is a bacterial disease that usually spread through contaminated water. Modern sewage and water treatment eliminated cholera in industrialized countries.
Hó͘-lia̍t-la sī chi̍t-chióng sè-khún chi̍t-pēⁿ it-poaⁿ ùi hō͘ u-jiám ê chúi thoân-pò͘. Hiān-tāi chúi-âm-kóng kah chúi chhú-lí tī kang-gia̍p-hòa kok-ka siau-bia̍t hó͘-lia̍t-la ah.
Chronic fatigue syndrome is very complicated disease that refers to a condition of fatigue that can not be explained by any underlying medical condition.
Bān-sèng nńg-sng chèng-hāu-kûn sī chi̍t-chióng chiok hok-cha̍p ê pēⁿ. Sī kóng chit-má ê i-ha̍k bô-hoat-tō͘ kái-sek ê nńg-sng.
Chronic kidney disease refers to a gradual loss of kidney function. The most common cause is untreated diabetes mellitus.
Bān-sèng io-chí pēⁿ sī kóng bān-bān-á sit-khì io-chí ê ki-lêng. Siōng chia̍p-khòaⁿ ê goan-in sī thn̂g-jiō-chèng bô tī-liâu.
Cirrhosis describes a condition where the liver is malfunctioning due to long-term damage; normal liver tissue is replaced with scar tissue.
Koaⁿ-ngē-hòa sī kóng koaⁿ tī tn̂g-kî siong-hāi tiong piàn-chó ki-lêng put-choân. It-poaⁿ ê koaⁿ cho͘-chit hō͘ ōaⁿ-chò khî-ê cho͘-chit.
Mn̂g-chín khui-mn̂g ê sî-kan kàu ah!

Coeliac disease is an autoimmune disorder where the immune system reacts to dietary gluten present in wheat, rye and barley. The reaction causes inflammation in the small intestines and thus malabsorption of nutrients.

Coeliac-pēⁿ sī chi̍t-chióng chū-sin bián-e̍k chi̍t-pēⁿ. Bián-e̍k hē-thóng tùi be̍h-á, o͘-be̍h kah tōa-be̍h chè-chō ê chia̍h-mi̍h lāi ê pho͘-chit hoán-èng. Chit-khoán hoán-èng tì-sú sió-tn̂g hoat-iām, siōng-bóe hō͘ chu-ióng ê khip-siu put-liông.
Congratulations, you placed your first object!
Contact dermatitis is a localized rash or irritation of the skin caused by contact to an allergen or irritant.
Chiap-chhiok-sèng phôe-hu-iām sī kio̍k-pō͘ phôe-hu ē chhut chín a̍h-sī chhì-kek. Che sī chi̍t-chióng bong-tio̍h kòe-bín-goân a̍h-sī chhì-kek-bu̍t ê pēⁿ.
Crohn's disease is an inflammatory bowel disease that affects the entire intestine. The exact cause is unknown, however, it is evident that there are genetic, environmental and autoimmune components.
Crohn-sī pēⁿ sī chi̍t-chióng ē éng-hióng kui-ê tn̂g-á ê hoat-iām-sèng tn̂g-á pēⁿ. Chèng-khak ê goan-in iáu-koh m̄-chai. M̄-koh, ū chèng-kù kóng ki-in, khoân-kéng kah chū-thé-bián-e̍k iú-koan.
Lí kám kah-ì góa ê pēⁿ-īⁿ?
Do you really want to send this patient to another hospital?
Lí kám chin-sim beh sàng chi̍t-ê hoān-chiá kàu pa̍t-ê pēⁿ-īⁿ?
Doudenitis is an inflammation of the lining of the duodenum; the first part of the small intestine, which is 12 inches long and curved into the C-shape.
Cha̍p-jī-chí-tn̂g-iām sī cha̍p-jī-chí-tn̂g lāi-bīn hoat-iām. Tiō sī sió-tn̂g ê thâu-chêng 12 eng-chhùn tn̂g koh oan-khiau kàu C hêng ê só͘-chai.
Drugs in various forms used to treat various bacterial infections.
Che io̍h-á ū chiok chē hêng-sek ē-sái tī-liâu sè-khún kám-jiám.
Eating undercooked beef can cause infection.
Chia̍h bô-se̍k ê gû-bah ū khó-lêng thoân-jiám.
Eating undercooked pork can cause infection.
Chia̍h bô-se̍k ê ti-bah ū khó-lêng thoân-jiám.
Esophageal varices are abnormally enlarged veins within the esophagus.
Chia̍h-tō-chēng-me̍h-liû sī chia̍h-tō lāi ê chēng-me̍h m̄-chū-jiân ê pûi-tōa.
Esophageal varices are abnormally enlarged veins within the esophagus. They are usually caused by portal hypertension due to existing liver disease.
Chia̍h-tō-chēng-me̍h-liû sī chia̍h-tō lāi ê chēng-me̍h m̄-chū-jiân ê pûi-tōa. Che it-poaⁿ sī hoān-chiá ê koaⁿ-pēⁿ thàu-kòe bûn-chēng-me̍h tì-sú ê.
Esophagitis is an inflammation of the oesophageal lining, often caused by acid reflux.
Chia̍h-tō-iām sī chia̍h-tō lāi-bīn hoat-iām, it-poaⁿ sī in-ūi ūi-sng-tò-lâu

Gallstones, also called cholelithiasis, are concretions of usually made from bilirubin, bile acids and calcium formed in the gall bladder. Gallstones usually do not cause symptoms, however, if they block the bile duct they can cause a variety of serious conditions.

Táⁿ-kiat-chio̍h mā kiò-chò táⁿ-chio̍h-chèng. Táⁿ-chio̍h it-poaⁿ sī bilirubin, táⁿ-chiap-sng kah tī táⁿ-lông lāi hêng-sêng ē khā-lú-siúm chek-chū ē. Táⁿ-kiat-chio̍h it-poaⁿ bô siaⁿh cheng-thâu, m̄-koh nā-sī chó͘-gāi táⁿ-kńg ē tì-sú chiok chē chiok giâm-tiōng ē tāi-chì.
Gastritis is an inflammation or erosion of the stomach's lining.
Ūi-iām sī ūi lāi-bīn hoat-iām a̍h-sī húi-nōa khì ah.

Gastritis is an inflammation or erosion of the stomach's lining. It is caused by; bad nutrition, excessive alcohol use, or excessive use of some medications. Treatment consists of protone pump inhibitors and discontinuation of alcohol or drugs that cause the symptoms.

Ūi-iām sī ūi lāi-bīn hoat-iām a̍h-sī húi-nōa khì ah. Êng-ióng bô-kàu, lim siuⁿ-chē chiú a̍h-sī chia̍h io̍h-á siuⁿ chhiau-kòe ah lóng ē tì-sú chit-khoán pēⁿ. Tī-liâu hong-hoat pau-hâm proton chúi-hia̍p-á ap-chè-che kah mài kè-siok chia̍h tì-sú chit-khoán pēⁿ ê mi̍h-kiāⁿ, pí-jū lim chiú a̍h-sī chia̍h io̍h-á.
Giardia infection is one of the most common waterborne intestinal infections. Giardias can be transmitted through direct contact with infected individuals or by ingesting contaminated food.
[fuzzy]Giardia chèng sī siōng chia̍p-khòaⁿ ê chúi-hē tn̂g-tō kám-jiám. Giardias ē-sái keng-iû ti̍t-chiap chiap-chhiok
Glomerulonephritis refers to inflammation of the filtering unit of the kidneys. It can be caused by an infection or autoimmunity.
Si-kiû-thé-io-chí-iām sī kóng io-chí lāi lū jiō ê tan-ūi hoat-iām. Kám-jiám a̍h-sī chū-sin bián-e̍k lông ū khó-lêng tì-sú chit-khoán pēⁿ.
Golfer's elbow, also known as medial epicondylitis, is characterized by radiating pain from the inside of the elbow to the wrist.
Golúhu tiú mā kiò-chò "lāi-pêng téng-khò-iām". Che pēⁿ ê thiàⁿ ē ūi tiú lāi hòng-siā kàu chhiú-óaⁿ.

Golfer's elbow, also known as medial epicondylitis, is characterized by radiating pain from the inside of the elbow to the wrist. The condition is caused by performing repetitive movements resulting in irritation of the muscles and tendons responsible for said movements.
Golúhu tiú mā kiò-chò "lāi-pêng téng-khò-iām". Che pēⁿ ê thiàⁿ ē ūi tiú lāi hòng-siā kàu chhiú-óaⁿ. It-ti̍t hoan ê tōng-chok ē tì-sú chit-khoán chêng-hêng, hō͘ kun-bah kah kiàn siōng-chē ê chhì-kek.
Grave's disease is an endocrine disease where the thyroid gland produces thyroid hormones in excess.
Grave-sī-pēⁿ sī chi̍t-chióng ê pēⁿ, ē hō͘ kah-chōng-chôaⁿ chè-chō siuⁿ chhiau-kòe ê kah-chōng-chôaⁿ ho-lú-bóng.
Hashimoto's thyroiditis is an autoimmune disease where the immune system gradually destroys the thyroid gland.
Hashimoto-sī-kah-chōng-chôaⁿ-iām sī chi̍t-chióng chū-sin bián-e̍k pēⁿ. Bián-e̍k hē-thóng ē bān-bān-á phò-hāi kah-chōng-chôaⁿ.
Have 30 patients under your care undergo X-ray examination.
Have 30 patients under your care undergo X-ray examination.
Hay fever, medically known as allergic rhinitis, is an inflammation in the nose caused by an allergic reaction to an allergen in the air, such as pollen.
Ta-chháu-jia̍t, i-ha̍k siōng kiò-chò kòe-bín ka-tap-jî. Sī chi̍t-chióng tùi khang-khùi tiong kòe-bín-goân hoat-seng kòe-bín hoán-èng tì-sú ê phiⁿ-á hoat-iām. Kòe-bín-goân chhiūⁿ-kóng hoe-hún.
Helicobacter pylori is a bacteria present in the upper gastrointestinal tract.
Helicobacter pylori sī chi̍t-chióng chhut-hiān tī ūi-tn̂g-kńg téng-bīn ê sè-khún.
Helicobacter pylori is a bacteria present in the upper gastrointestinal tract. It is the main cause of peptic ulcers.
Helicobacter pylori sī chi̍t-chióng chhut-hiān tī ūi-tn̂g-kńg téng-bīn ê sè-khún. I sī siau-hòa-sèng-ùi-iông ê chú-iàu goan-in.

Hepatic fibrosis represents an accumulation of scar tissue in the liver. The scar tissue can be the result of long term inflammation or another liver disease caused by viruses, bacterias, malnutrition or alcohol abuse etc. If left untreated it causes cirrhosis.

Koaⁿ chhiam-î-chèng sī kóng koaⁿ lāi ê khî-ê cho͘-chit thiok-chek. He khî-ê cho͘-chit hoān-sè sī tn̂g-kî hoat-iām a̍h-sī pa̍t-ê iû pēⁿ-to̍k a̍h-sī sè-khún tì-sú ê koaⁿ-pēⁿ, chu-ióng put-liâng a̍h-sī siong-chiú téng-téng ín-khí ê. Nā bô tī-liâu ē tì-sú koaⁿ-ngē-hòa.
Hepatitis A virus spreads through feces and usually occurs in areas with poor sanitation or hygiene.
A-hêng koaⁿ-iām pēⁿ-to̍k sī ūi sái thoân-khui, it-poaⁿ sī tī ōe-seng bô-hó ê só͘-chai hoat-seng.
Hepatitis B virus spreads via blood, sexual contact or from mother to child.
B-hêng koaⁿ-iām ê thoân-jiám sī ūi hoeh, sio-kàn, a̍h-sī bú thoân hō͘ gín-á.
Hepatitis refers to a viral infection of the liver.
Koaⁿ-iām sī kòng koaⁿ hō͘ pēⁿ-to̍k kám-jiám.
Hepatitis refers to a viral infection of the liver. Hepatitis A virus spreads through feces and usually occurs in areas with poor sanitation or hygiene.
Koaⁿ-iām sī kòng koaⁿ hō͘ pēⁿ-to̍k kám-jiám. A-hêng koaⁿ-iām pēⁿ-to̍k sī ūi sái thoân-khui, it-poaⁿ sī tī ōe-seng bô-hó ê só͘-chai hoat-seng.
Hepatitis refers to a viral infection of the liver. Hepatitis B virus spreads via blood, sexual contact or from mother to child.

Hì-kiat-hu̍t sī chi̍t-chióng thoân-jiám-sèng chin kiông ê pēⁿ. Chit-ê pēⁿ goân-chū chi̍t-ê kiò-chò Mycobacterium tuberculosis ê sè-khún, i chú-iàu éng-hióng hì-chōng, m̄-koh mā ē thoân-pò͘ kàu pa̍t-ê chōng-khì, pí-jū tōa-náu khì.

Tularaemia is an infectious disease that mainly affects the skin, eyes, lymph nodes or lungs. It is caused by the Francisella tularensis bacteria. Tulareamia is highly contagious, potentially fatal, but can be treated effectively.

Thó͘-á-jia̍t sī chi̍t-chióng chú-iàu éng-hióng phôe-hu, ba̍k-chiu, Lîm-pa-chôaⁿ a̍h-sī hì ê pēⁿ. Che pēⁿ goân-chū chi̍t-chióng kiò-chò Francisella tularensis ê sè-khún. Tulareamia ê thoân-jiám-sèng chin kiông, ū khó-lêng tì-miā, m̄-koh mā ū chiok ū-hāu ê tī-liâu hong-hoat.
Typhoid fever is a bacterial disease that spreads through contaminated water and food. It is rare in industrialized countries.

UTF, or cystitis, is an infection of the bladder usually by E. coli; a type of bacteria commonly found in the gastrointestinal (GI) tract. It is a condition a hundred times more common in women due to a shorter urinary tract.

UTF (Jiō-kńg kám-jiám), mā kiò-chò phōng-kong-iām, it-poaⁿ sī phōng-kong òe-tio̍h tōa-tn̂g-kán-khún (E. coli). Chit-khoán sè-khún it-poaⁿ sī tī ūi-tn̂g-kńg lāi hoat-hiān. Cha-bó͘-lâng in-ūi khah té ê jiō-tō, tio̍h chit-khoán pēⁿ ê ki-hōe pí cha-po͘ koân pah pòe.

Ulcerative colitis is an inflammatory bowel disease that produces ulcers in the large intestine. The exact cause is unknown, however, it is evident that there are genetic, environmental and autoimmune components.
